Physical quantities that are distinct from primary electric power system variables and that have a direct impact on the generation, transmission, distribution, and consumption of electric power. They often serve as inputs to the electric power generation and consumption functions (e.g., wind speed, solar irradiance, and building occupancy).■\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
